# Project structure rules

- Use the existing folder layout; **don’t introduce new top-level patterns** without a strong reason.
- Prefer `@/` imports for anything in `src/` (alias is configured in `tsconfig` and `vite.config.ts`).

## Where code goes

- `src/modules/public/**`: public screens/features
- `src/modules/private/**`: authenticated screens/features
- `src/routes/**`: router/provider + route exports (single source of navigation)
- `src/components/**`: shared reusable components (cross-module)
- `src/components/ui/**`: shadcn/ui components and re-exports
- `src/api/**`: endpoint definitions + API helpers
- `src/types/**`: shared types (e.g. route typing)
- `src/providers/**`: React providers composition
- `src/layout/**`: app/page layout shells

## Export conventions

- Prefer **barrel exports** via `index.ts` inside `modules/*` and `routes/` to keep imports stable.
- Keep module internals private; only export the module entry surface from its `index.ts`.
